This plugin will automatically convert these supported _YouTube_ link and URL in the page and comment content to _YouTube_ video player:

 - `https://www.youtube.com/watch?v={$id}`
 - `https://www.youtube.com/v/{$id}`
 - `https://youtu.be/{$id}`
 - `https://www.youtube.com/embed/{$id}`

The _YouTube_ link and URL must be written on its own line by itself, with or without the `www`, with `http://` or `https://`.

All of [the available _YouTube_ player parameters](https://developers.google.com/youtube/player_parameters) can be used normally and will be applied automatically to the generated video frames.

### Additional Parameters

Name | Description
---- | -----------
`width` | Set custom video width.
`height` | Set custom video height.

**Example:**

~~~ .txt
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v={$id}&width=600&height=250
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v={$id}&width=600px&height=250px
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v={$id}&height=25%
~~~